<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 16 Militants Killed In Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people, including 16
militants and an Indian soldier, were killed as Indian security
forces stepped up anti-militant operations in Kashmir since Monday
evening, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
PTI quoted a source from the Border Security Force (BSF) as
saying that five unidentified militants were killed in a joint
operation by BSF and the army against the so-called militants in
Baramulla district of Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
A big cache of arms and ammunition including four AK assault
rifles, a grenade launcher and five rockets were recovered, the
BSF source said.
</P>
<P>
In a two-day operation in Kanzalwan sector of north Kashmir
which ended Monday, five more unidentified militants were killed,
according to an Indian Army spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Police said security forces killed four militants at Bagtoore-
gurez in Baramulla sector Monday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
