<HEADLINE> Arafat to Visit Egypt Saturday for Talks on Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
will visit Egypt on Saturday for more consultations with President
Hosni Mubarak on the peace talks with Israel, the official Middle
East News Agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It will be Arafat's fifth visit to Egypt since the Camp David
summit ended on July 25 in the United States without reaching a
final Israeli-Palestinian peace accord. The Palestinian leader was
last in Egypt on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted diplomatic sources as saying that the two
leaders would discuss all the ideas and proposals put forward by
the concerned parties to help advance the peace process and seek
ways of overcoming the current challenges.
</P>
<P>
Israel's acting Foreign Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami also is to visit
Egypt Thursday for talks with Mubarak amid intensive Egyptian
contacts with all parties concerned in the peace process, the news
agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
