<HEADLINE> S.Leone Rebels Pledge Cooperation With UNAMSIL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone's rebel Revolutionary
United Front (RUF) has pledged to cooperate with the United
Nations Peace Mission in Sierra Leone (UNAMSIL) to resume the
peace process under the Lome Peace Accord signed last year,
according to a report reaching here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The assurance was made following a meeting between the RUF and
presidents Olusegun Obasanjo of Nigeria, Charles Taylor of Liberia
and Oumar Konare of Mali, who is also the chairman of the Economic
Community of West African States (ECOWAS), in the Liberian capital
Monrovia on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to a press communique released by the RUF after the
meeting, the RUF would cooperate with the UNAMSIL in the
deployment of UN peace-keepers in the RUF-controlled areas to
ensure the success of the disarmament program in particular, and
the peace process in general as mandated in the Lome Peace Accord.
</P>
<P>
The RUF welcomed the Sierra Leone government's decision to
release about 170 RUF fighters in detention as a step of
confidence building.
</P>
<P>
In return, the RUF decided to hand over the equipment it
captured from the UNAMSIL. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
