<HEADLINE> Dalai Lama Inappropriate to Attend Peace Summit: Chinese Religious Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, August 24 (Xinhua) - The Dalai Lama is a turmoil-
maker instead of peace-maker and is thus absolutely inappropriate
to be invited or allowed to attend the upcoming Millenium World
Peace Summit of Religious and Spiritual Leaders to be held at the
United Nations Headquarters, a Chinese religious delegation said
here today.
</P>
<P>
"The issue of Dalai Lama is closely related to the emotional
feeling of the Chinese people and the sovereignty of the state,
and the Chinese people have, as always, been resolute in this
issue," said Jamyang Losang Jigme Tubdain Qoigyi Nyima, top Living
Buddha of Tibetan Buddhism and member of the delegation, which
will attend the peace summit.
</P>
<P>
"Some people want to make it an issue and trying to split Tibet
from China and interfere in China's internal affairs," he said.
</P>
<P>
Bishop Michael Fu Tieshan, head of the delegation, said that
the peace summit should be for peace-makers, instead of for
trouble- or turmoil-makers.
</P>
<P>
