<HEADLINE> Syrian President to Visit Egypt in September: Mubarak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Bashar al-Assad is
to visit Egypt in September, Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak made the announcement during a meeting with Egyptian
university students in the Mediterranean port city of Alexandria,
the country's official Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Bashar's visit to Egypt will take place in the second half of
next month, Mubarak was quoted as saying by the news agency.
</P>
<P>
Reports have initially said that Bashar was to visit Egypt at
the end of this month as part of an Arab tour, which will also take
him to Bahrain and Saudi Arabia. It will be Bashar's first trip
abroad since taking office last month after the death of his
father, Hafez al-Assad, in June.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak said Bashar is ready to restart peace talks with Israel
on the basis of complete Israeli withdrawal from Syria's lands
occupied in the 1967 Mideast War, the news agency added. He
reiterated Egypt's support for the Syrian position.
</P>
<P>
After a brief resumption in December following a hiatus of
nearly four years, Syria and Israel froze again their peace
negotiations due to failure to overcome differences over the return
of the Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the possibility of holding an Arab summit, supported
by Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq Shareh during his visit to Egypt
on Monday, the Egyptian president said it could be convened "this
year or at the beginning of next year."
</P>
<P>
After meeting with Mubarak, Shareh called on Arab leaders to
hold a summit to seek ways of ending a "wretched situation of
disunity" in the Arab world for the benefit of the Arab nation and
peace and stability in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The last Arab summit was held in 1996 in Cairo. 
</P>
