<HEADLINE> Vietnam: End U.N. Embargo Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam demands an immediate end
to the U.N. embargo and military activities against Iraq, the
Vietnamese Foreign Ministry said Wednesday
</P>
<P>
Spokeswoman Phan Thuy Thanh made the remarks while answering
Party daily Nhan Dan (the People) about Vietnam's stance on the
10th anniversary of the United Nations' imposition of embargo
against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 10 years, Thanh said, the embargo has caused
disasters to the Iraqi people. Nearly 1.5 million Iraqis, most of
them children, women and elderly people, died of hunger and
medicine shortage.
</P>
<P>
She said the U.N. continuation of its embargo against Iraq
constitutes an inhumane act, violating human rights and running
counter to morality.
</P>
<P>
She affirmed that the Vietnamese people, together with peace-
and justice-loving people in the world, demand an immediate end to
the embargo and military activities against Iraq so that the Iraqi
people will soon bring their lives back to normal and re-build
their country. 
</P>
