<HEADLINE> Singapore's Consumer Price Index Rises in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's consumer price
index in July rose by 0.5 percent over the previous month and 1.2
percent over the same period of last year, according to data
released Wednesday by the Department of Statistics (SDS).
</P>
<P>
Except the 0.2 percent dip in food prices, all other group
indices went up.
</P>
<P>
The most significant price hikes were seen in clothing prices
which went up 2.3 percent and in cost of education which advanced
by 1.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Dearer petrol and higher taxi fares helped raise the costs of
transport and communication by 0.8 percent, while health care
costs and prices of miscellaneous items inched up by 0.1 percent
and 0.2 percent respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
