<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- One hundred Hong Kong students
were appointed at an appointment ceremony Wednesday as Student
Ambassadors for promoting Hong Kong's international profile while
studying overseas.
</P>
<P>
These Student Ambassadors were appointed under the Hong Kong
Student Ambassador Program 2000, a program designed to give
students who are about to further their studies overseas.
</P>
<P>
Eric Li, Council Member of the Hong Kong Federation of Youth
Groups led the Student Ambassadors in a pledge to do their best to
promote Hong Kong. These Student Ambassadors will be studying in
universities in the United States, the United Kingdom, Australia,
Belgium, Denmark and India.
</P>
<P>
The three-week intensive training program organized for the
Student Ambassadors includes visits to government departments,
public organizations, financial institutions, local businesses and
industries, educational and social service institutions, IT
companies and infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Student Ambassador Program is organized by the
Hong Kong Federation of Youth Group in association with Hong Kong
Tourist Association. 
