<HEADLINE> Malaysia Attempts to Set World Tree Planting Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia attempts to plant
100,000 tress within a minute in a bid to create a new world
record.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian attempt would take place on October 15 at various
places throughout the country simultaneously, Bernama news agency
reported Wednesday quoting Housing and Local Government Minister
Ong Ka Ting.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamd will lead 100,000 people in the
attempt which would start as soon as they receive the signal via
radio from the campaign's launch site here.
</P>
<P>
The attempt will be part of the "New Millennium Gift of Trees
for the Nation" campaign which is a continuation of the "Gift of
Trees to Green the Nation" campaign launched in 1996, the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
The 1996 campaign has succeeded in getting 2.3 million trees
planted against the target of three million trees by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
The attempt is being organized by the Malaysian Nature Society,
Forest Research Institute of Malaysia, Lions Club, One Earth
Enterprise and the Malaysian Private Property Valuers and
Consultants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
