<HEADLINE> Philippine VP: No Asylum for Abu Sayyaf Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Vice President Gloria
Macapagal Arroyo said Wednesday that she is not in favor of
granting asylum to the terrorist Abu Sayyaf group leaders.
</P>
<P>
Arroyo told reporters here that the recent events hounding the
Southern Mindanao showed that granting an asylum to the Abu Sayyaf
is not the proper measure.
</P>
<P>
"I am not in favor of granting asylum to the Abu Sayyaf leaders,
they must face the consequences," said Arroyo, who is also
Secretary of Social Welfare and Development.
</P>
<P>
The asylum to be granted by foreign countries is reportedly one
of the several conditions that Abu Sayyaf leaders Ghalib "
Commander Robot" Andang and Mujib Susukan were asking in exchange
for their captive's release.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist group was supposed to release on August 20 their
remaining hostages but, at the last minute, they backed out for
fear of massive military operations against them.
</P>
<P>
Abu Sayyaf extremists are still holding in their hands nearly
30 hostages, some of them being western tourists abducted in April
from Malaysia. 
