<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Estrada Orders Soldiers to Stand Against Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Following a massive attack on
soldiers by the New People's Army (NPA) in the central Philippines
on Monday, Philippine President Joseph Estrada has ordered
soldiers in NPA-active areas to stand their ground.
</P>
<P>
Defense Secretary Orlando Mercado said Wednesday the president
wants residents in these areas protected against the abusive "
leftist guerrillas."
</P>
<P>
"As far as the president is concerned, we have to stand our
ground. We must defend the rights not only of Mindanao residents,
but also of those threatened by leftist guerrillas," Mercado said
in a radio interview.
</P>
<P>
NPA guerrillas ambushed soldiers in the central province of
Negros Occidental on Monday, killing at least 17 on the spot while
another died under treatment.
</P>
<P>
Mercado said the NPA appears to be stepping up its attacks, in
line with the order of its founding chairman Jose Sison from the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Reyes said Wednesday that he has ordered a
massive manhunt against NPA rebels responsible for the said ambush.
</P>
<P>
Reyes assured the people of Negros Occidental that there is
nothing to fear as the situation has already been under control.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
