Tourism Exposition closed today in Yanji, a scenic city in the
Yanbian Korean Autonomous Prefecture, northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Most of the people from China's Korean ethnic group live in the
1,350-square-kilometer prefecture, accounting for 58.8 percent of
the local population and Yanji, the prefecture's capital, is a
major Chinese city open to countries in northeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Hosted by the city government, the exposition showed the world
the folk customs of the people from the Korean ethic group and the
rich tourism resources in this area.
</P>
