<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Plunges 9.26 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market
index plunged 7.35 points, or 9.26 percent, to 72.05 points on
Wednesday, after it was beaten to an intraday nadir of 71.70
points in early afternoon, well below its 10-day moving average.
</P>
<P>
Daily turnover was 87.65 million US dollars, which was 7.67
million or 8.05 percent less than Tuesday's total, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
Not ready to overcome its sudden reversal starting yesterday
afternoon, the market was succumbed to further sell-off for most
of the day as profit-takers dragged stocks in all areas sharply
down with follow-through moves.
</P>
<P>
There was no leadership today as breadth figures were running
decisively in favor of negativity. Fifty-four losers dominate the
market, with the remaining one suspended from trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 players dived to the daily price floor,
including Goods and Materials Sanmao, Dazhong Taxi, Friendship,
Waigaoqiao, Zhenhua, Lujiazui, Chlor Alkali, Worldbest Kama,
Jintai, P and T and China Travel.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the slide, where sellers made
strong presence, could be curbed to some extent if buyers mount up
to back up. The market has got a respite in its meltdown in the
late day, an encouraging performance thus far as traders have
shown a little inclination to reverse the bearish trend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
