<HEADLINE> Shanghai Composite Index Down On Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
ended at 2057.92 points, down 16.78 points or 0.81 percent on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was greatly expanded to 22.28 billion yuan, a new
high after March 6, up 49.22 percent compared to yesterday's 14.93
billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Following yesterday's downward trend, the Shanghai composite
index dived to 2064.05 points after opening this morning, down 10.
65 points or 0.5 percent compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
Although the index rebounded, supported by the 20-day average
line, investors' buying was not active. Therefore, the index
plunged through the psychological line of 2,000 points at the
afternoon opening, touching 1,980 points, the lowest level in a
month. Then the market started to rebound not long after the
afternoon opening, led by big player-held shares.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that the market index dropped over 100
points with a big correction after the index reached above 2000
points last month. And the turnover also reached a new high since
March 6.
</P>
<P>
Three companies reached their ceilings, including Shanghai
Donghai Co., Ltd., Jiangsu Chunlan Refrigerating Equipment Stock
Co., Ltd. and Kaile Plastic Pipe Material Co., Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi Bailong Co., Ltd. was the biggest loser today with its
price down 5.83 percent to 22.60 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the A-share market is likely
to rally tomorrow.  
</P>
