<HEADLINE> Heavy Fog Shrouds North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Northern China was covered
by heavy fog this morning, causing some road accidents on
expressways.
</P>
<P>
From 5 o'clock this morning, heavy fog fell on Beijing and
Tianjin municipalities as well as Hebei and Shanxi provinces. The
visibility along expressways and railways was no more than 20
meters.
</P>
<P>
Four road accidents have been reported along the Shijiazhuang
to Xingtai Expressway. One person was killed and two were
hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Hebei Provincial Meteorological Station warned
that fog will possibly cover northern China again tonight.
