<HEADLINE> China to Reform Prosecution System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- China will introduce a series of
reforms in its prosecution system this year to ensure justice and
the independent rights of prosecutors.
</P>
<P>
Since early this year, chief prosecutors have been made
responsible for individual cases. So far, the practice has been
adopted by 2,195 procuratorates across the country.
</P>
<P>
According to today's "People's Daily", the reforms will include
the public demonstration of evidences prior to the court hearing.
</P>
<P>
In addition, new prosecuting document forms will be introduced
into procuratorates within the year. 
