work on a series of cultural relics today.
</P>
<P>
Local government officials said the efforts are to remind
visitors and local residents of the city's long history. The
project will last three years and cost 330 million yuan (about 39.
6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
A dozen of cultural relics, including the Temple of Heaven, the
Confucius Temple and the Ruins of the Yuanmingyuan Imperial Garden,
have been listed in this year's maintenance plan.
</P>
<P>
Beijing owns over 7,000 cultural relics, with 24 under State
protection. Since the 1980s, the Chinese capital has invested 40
million yuan in repairs and renovation of these cultural treasures.
