<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Ericsson signed here today a
series of contracts China Unicom to supply equipment for Unicom's
GSM projects at its five provincial branches.
</P>
<P>
Under the contracts, valued at 176 million U.S. dollars,
Ericsson will supply equipment and services for China Unicom's GSM
900 networks expansion in the five provinces of Jilin, Sichuan,
Jiangsu, Anhui and Hubei.
</P>
<P>
This will increase the total capacity of Ericsson's GSM
networks in these five provinces to 3.83 million subscribers, an
Ericsson spokesman said.
</P>
