<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Closes Down Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
closed at 627.16 points on Wednesday, down 6.08 points or 0.96
percent compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 18.66 billion yuan, 37.71 percent more than
Tuesday's 13.55 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Following yesterday's trend, the Shenzhen composite index
dived to open at 629.18 points this morning, down 4.06 points or 0.
6 percent compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
Although the index rebounded, supported by the 20-day average
line in the morning, investors' buying was inactive. Therefore,
the index dropped fast after the afternoon opening, and touched
601.47 points, the lowest level in a month. Then the market
started to rebound shortly, led by big player-held stocks.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the market index dropped over five
percent since the index exceeded 600 points from last month.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the A-share market is likely
to continue its rebound tomorrow, but the 636-point level was its
resistance level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
