<HEADLINE> 2nd Lead: Indonesian President Forms New Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian president Abdurrahman
Wahid announced here Wednesday his new cabinet with significant
changes. Some departments were liquidated or merged.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet formation consists of 26 personnel, namely two
Coordinating ministers, sixteen ministers, five state ministers,
and three junior ministers.
</P>
<P>
Under the new cabinet, Wahid placed Susilo Bambang Yudoyono as
Coordinating Minister for politics, social and security, while
Rizal Ramli as Coordinating Minister for economic affairs.
</P>
<P>
Yudoyono previously was Minister of Mine and Energy while Ramli
was Chief of the State Logistic Agency (Bulog). 
</P>
