<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices experienced one-
percent plunge on Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as investors
failed to react to U.S. Federal Reserve's decision to hold
interest rates steady.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gave up 20.06 points to
end at 2,190.45 points in thin dealings.
</P>
<P>
The market volume amounted to only 351.36 million units valued
at 542.48 million Singapore dollars (about 315.85 million U.S.
dollars). Declining issues overwhelmed advancers by 249 to 84 with
230 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Ionics was the most active stock with a turnover of 24.40
million units. Trek was the second most heavily traded stock with
16.36 million shares done. Sunlight was the next with 15.89
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH, SPH 100 and SembLog topped the day's gainers list as they
rose by 50 cents to 28.80 and 10.80 Singapore dollars respectively
at close. ShangAsia put on 25 cents to finish at 8.30 Hong Kong
dollars. CSA added 11 cents to end at 3.02 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
PacCent was the biggest loser of the day, incurring a loss of
150 cents to close at 22.30 Singapore dollars. SIA and SIA 200
slipped 40 cents each to finish at 18.60 and 18.70 Singapore
dollars separately. Chartered and Creative 50 retreated 30 cents
to end at 14.30 and 38.20 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that U.S. Federal Reserve's decision to leave
interest rates unchanged failed to boost the market and no factor
could support the recent upward trend.
</P>
<P>
They noted that shares of the Singapore Airline (SIA) fell due
to profit-taking and concerns that rising fuel prices could erode
its profits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
