<DOCNO> XIE20000823.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> T-bond Trade Slackens on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond trade narrowed
today while bonds stayed stable at current prices. Transaction
value totaled 1.33 billion yuan, down 425 million yuan from
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
China's domestic stock market expanded the sharp slump today.
But investors were seen hesitated to transfer capital into fixed
income T-bonds, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009704 leapt 0.30 percent to stay at 145.65 yuan with the
yield down 0.05 percentage points to 3.82 percent, still the
highest all outstanding bonds.
</P>
<P>
All the other bonds changed little at the close prices.
</P>
<P>
As money was fleeing away from stocks when securities plunged,
and there was no expansion in the trade in treasuries, the eased
money supply led the repurchasing market to slack.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
repurchasing transactions contracted by 456 million yuan to 1.85
billion yuan. Meanwhile, the interest rate of the three-day
repurchasing agreement slipped by 0.04 percentage points to 2.95
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
