<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Index down on Wednesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market
index closed at 127.19 points on Wednesday, down 4.46 points or 3.
39 percent compared with that on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen B-share index climbed up after it opened low and
hit 131.25 points. Then the index went downwards to 120.24 points
in early afternoon, which was today's lowest level, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 390.22 million Hong Kong dollars, which was 164.35
million Hong Kong dollars or 29.64 percent less than that on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Although the index rebounded this afternoon, the negative
result kept unchanged, as the market met some profit-taking
pressure.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the negative market caused by
profit takers is not likely to be reversed easily in the near term.
</P>
