<HEADLINE> China, Nepal Further Customs Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lhasa, August 23 (Xinhua) -- China and Nepal agreed to tighten
customs control at the border areas and a memorandum to this end
was signed here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Weimin, deputy director of the Lhasa Customs Office, and
Risi Ram Lamichhane, the visiting Nepalese customs director,
signed the document at the 13th meeting between the two countries'
border customs.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, they exchanged views on further customs
cooperation and the impact of Nepal's new trade policy on
bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed to increase efforts to crack down on smuggling
at the border areas.
</P>
<P>
The Nepalese customs delegation, led by Lamichhane, arrived in
Lhasa for the meeting last Saturday.  
