<P>
WELLINGTON -- The New Zealand dollar has sunk to all-time low
against the U.S. dollar. It fell below 44 U.S. cents for the first
time in more than 15 years Wednesday, trading at 43.47 U.S. cents
after losing 1.53 U.S.cents overnight.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thailand will double its oil imports from Oman to
prevent domestic gasoline prices hike from affecting the country's
economic recovery, Thai Industry Minister Suwat Liptapallop said
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Suwat told reporters that his ministry had submitted a bigger
oil order, increased from 17,000 barrels a day to 34,000 barrels a
day, to Oman's energy ministry through the Omani Embassy to
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SHENYANG, CHINA -- A forum themed with new economic development
and digitization in industrial cities opened Tuesday in this
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The three-day forum will focus on a series of economic and high-
tech topics including e-business, enterprise reform, network
construction, new economy and digitization.
</P>
