<P>
DHAKA -- Bangladeshi money changers Tuesday suggested
reintroduction of "auction sale" of foreign currency to check
underground transfer and encourage official inflow of foreign
remittance to raise the country's poor foreign exchange reserve.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's Foreign exchange reserve was 2.03 billion U.S.
dollars when the present government assumed power in 1996, then it
came down to 1.62 billion dollars in May this year and 1.4 billion
by now, Bangladesh Money Changers Association (BMCA) president
Kefayet Ullah Masud told a press conference here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG -- Two Chinese oil giants have decided to join hands
with the Hong Kong-based conglomerate Hutchison Whampoa to build
the first e-commerce portal for focusing specially on the demands
of oil and gas industry in China.
</P>
<P>
PetroChina Company Limited, China National Petroleum
Corporation (CNPC) and Hutchison Whampoa Limited announced Tuesday
the signing of a memorandum of understanding for the launch of the
portal.
</P>
<P>
In its first phase, the portal will establish a comprehensive e-
marketplace for all oil and gas products and related services in
China.
</P>
