<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto to be Tried Next Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian former President
Soeharto will be tried for corruption case next Friday, August 31
at 10;00 a.m.(local time), an official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chief of the South Jakarta District Court, Lalu Mariyun said in
a press conference that, "Former President Soeharto will be
brought to justice on August 31 on Friday. The trial will be
conducted at the agriculture ministry building instead of at the
South Jakarta District Court building," Mariyun said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the decision was made for the sake of
security reasons and "to meet the people aspiration who wish to
see the trial process," he added.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that there will be a lot of spectators during the
trial.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chief of the South Jakarta Police Senior
Superintendent Edward Aritonang said on the same occasion that the
police is ready to safeguard the trial process, adding that his
side will deploy its personnel around the location of the
agriculture building.
</P>
<P>
But he didn't said in detail on the number of security
personnel which will be deployed to safeguard the trial.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto is principally charged with violating article 1 (a) of
Law No. 3/1971 on corruption for deliberately enriching himself at
the state's expense.
</P>
<P>
He is also subject to subsidiary charges as provided for by
article 1 (b) of corruption law under which a defendant may be
convicted for abusing of power so as to cause losses to the state.
</P>
<P>
In another development, just days ahead the trial, Chief of the
Investigation Team into former president Soeharto, RIS Pandopatan
Sihombing was replaced on Wednesday by Sudibyo Saleh.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman of the attorney's office said that the replacement of
Sihombing was normal.
</P>
<P>
"That is a normal tour of duty," he told Xinhua, adding that
there is also not a political motive behind the replacement.
</P>
</TEXT>
