<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafter Leads Seeds to Advance in Hamlet Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Australian Patrick Rafter led
the field of seeds to advance on Tuesday in the Hamlet Open men's
tennis tournament after receiving byes in the first round of the
415,200 U.S. dollars event in Commack, New York.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, seeded seventh, struggled to go through from one set
down after he survived with a 6-7 (3-7), 7-5, 7-6 (10-8) victory
over Stefan Koubek of Austria.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch Richard Krajicek, seeded 11th, won with straight sets
following a 6-4, 6-1 rout over Bohdan Ulihrach of the Czech
Republic.
</P>
<P>
Sixth seed Juan Carlos Ferrero of Spain defeated Alexander Popp
of Russia 3-6, 6-4, 6-2 while eighth seed Younes El Aynaoui of
Morocco eliminated Gianluca Pozzi of Italy 7-6 (7-5), 6-3.
</P>
</TEXT>
