<HEADLINE> Changchun Film Festival Opens Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 23 (Xinhua) -- In order to let more people
know about the progress of the Fifth Changchun Film Festival in
northeastern Jilin Province, a Chinese-language website with the
address: http//www.cc-film.com, was launched recently.
</P>
<P>
Website content includes features and talks about the
development of the Changchun film festival, masterpiece film show
and an on-line chat room. Fans will not only get the latest
information on the film festival, but will also be able to take
part in on-line discussions and vote for their favorite film,
favorite film star and favorite music score for the film.
</P>
<P>
Cui Yongquan, organizing member of the film festival, said the
website was created to make good use of mass media and to connect
with the audience both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The festival, one of the three major film festivals in China,
opens today and lasts until August 26. 
