<HEADLINE> Good Social Environment Crucial for Preventing Juvenile Delinquency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A social environment favorable
for the growth of Chinese youths is crucial for preventing
juvenile delinquency in the country, according to a national
meeting on social problems.
</P>
<P>
Preventing and reducing juvenile delinquency concerns not only
the healthy growth of juveniles and the happiness of families, but
also the future of the nation, said Wang Shengjun, a senior
official with the law affairs department of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Wang urged local CPC committees and governments at all levels
to strengthen legal education among primary and secondary school
students and take practical measures to keep social stability, the
People's Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
All must be aimed at providing a social environment favorable
for the growth of juveniles in the country, Wang said at the
meeting, sponsored by the Central Commission for Comprehensive
Management of Social Problems.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials from the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme
People's Procuratorate, the Ministry of Public Security, the
Ministry of Education and other central government departments and
social organizations attended the meeting and aired their views on
how to prevent juvenile delinquency.  
</P>
