<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Resume Direct Flights to South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam Airline (VA) will resume
direct air flights from Hanoi to Seoul and from Ho Chi Minh City
to Seoul in October this year, the Construction and Transportation
Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese airline, which suspended the direct flights in
early 1998 after Southeastern and Eastern Asia was hit by an
economic crisis, will operate direct air routes between Seoul and
Hanoi three times a week and between Seoul and Ho Chi Minh City
five times a week.
</P>
<P>
At present, South Korea's Korean Air and Asiana Airlines each
operate five direct flights per week between Seoul and Ho Chi Minh
City. 
