<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- Asia will account for a growing proportion of
global auto industry demand and production for the future, but the
short-term picture remains less buoyant, according to a report
released Tuesday by Standard and Poor's.
</P>
<P>
In the next decade, vehicle demand in Asia, excluding Japan, is
expected to increase at a compound average annual rate of 8.3
percent to reach 14.8 million units in 2010, the report said. (
Asia-Auto Industry)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The Cyprus government on Tuesday warned foreigners
against buying the property left over by the Greek Cypriots who
were evicted by the Turkish Cypriot-controlled northern Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Anybody buying Greek Cypriot property in northern Cyprus
through illegal means should know they will not be able to keep it,
the Cyprus government warned. (Cyprus-Property)
</P>
