- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Federal Reserve, amid signs the
supercharged economy is finally beginning to slow, decided Tuesday
to leave key interest rates unchanged but said it remained
concerned about inflation in the future.
</P>
<P>
The decision by the Fed's policy-making Federal Open Market
Committee left the benchmark Federal funds target rate on
overnight loans among banks at 6.5 percent and the discount rate
on loans from the Federal Reserve system at 6.0 percent. (Cyprus-
Property)
</P>
