<HEADLINE> Uruguay's Trade Deficit Reaches 1.197 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay registered a trade
deficit of 1.197 billion U.S. dollars in the 12 months to June,
the Central Bank of Uruguay reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Uruguay's exports amounted to 2.29 billion
dollars and imports 3.487 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the previous corresponding period, Uruguay
recorded a 67.6 percent growth in exports to its main trade
destination, the bloc of North American Free Trade Agreement (
NAFTA) which is made up of the United States, Canada and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
While Uruguay's exports to Europe went down 17 percent, its
exports to Argentina and the rest of the world grew 9.1 percent
and 12.9 percent respectively. 
</P>
