<HEADLINE> Sotomayor Injures Left Leg at Viareggio Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 22 (Xinhua) -- High jump world record holder
Javier Sotomayor of Cuba injured his left leg on Tuesday and was
doubful for the upcoming Olympic Games in Sydney in Viareggio,
Italy.
</P>
<P>
Sotomayor, 32, strained left hamstring on his second attempt at
2.28 meters at the Viareggio meet.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban, who returned last week after serving half of a two-
year ban for a positive test for cocaine, won his first two meets
after comeback.
</P>
<P>
Sotomayor, who holds the world record of 2.45 meters, has been
eyeing the upcoming Olympics in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Fellow Cuban Ivan Pedroso, the reigning world long jump
champion, jumped to 8.10 meters to beat Jamaica's James Beckford,
whose best effort was 8.04 meters.
</P>
<P>
Fiona May of Italy, won the women's long jump, with a winning
effort of 6.74 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
