<HEADLINE> Typhoon Bilis to Hit East China Province At Noon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of
Xiamen in east China's Fujian Province has decided to give
government employees a one-day leave today as Typhoon Bilis is
expected to hit the city around noon.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen has already had heavy rains this morning and government
departments are prepared to deal with emergencies that may result
from the typhoon.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen's Ferry Service has suspended all shipping service today
and the Xiamen Airlines has canceled all scheduled flights.
</P>
<P>
Local observatory estimated that Xiamen's rainfall will reach
150-200 mm or even 300 mm in some areas.
</P>
<P>
Typhoon Bilis will be the severest to affect Xiamen this year,
local meteorological experts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000823.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,000-year-old Vinegar Town Even Prosperous Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese people love drinking tea
just like western people have special interest in coffee.
</P>
<P>
However, people in Langzhong, a 1,000-year-old small town in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, enjoy a quite different habit:
drinking vinegar instead of tea.
</P>
<P>
As a matter of fact, local people cannot go by without vinegar
in their daily life: using vinegar as a kind of soft drinks to
replace tea, using vinegar to entertain guests instead of alcohol
and tea, and even pour vinegar in cooked rice as a tonic or health-
care medicine to prevent the complication of certain diseases.
</P>
<P>
Located at the foot of the Daba Mountain and by the River of
Jialing, a tributary of the Yangtze River, Langzhong is home to
Baoning Vinegar, one of the four name brand vinegar products in
China.
</P>
<P>
China mainly produces three kinds of vinegar products. They
include the mature vinegar, which is brewed from sorghum at high
temperature, with Chencu (mature vinegar) of north China's Shanxi
province as the sample, the aromatic vinegar, brewed from
glutinous rice at low temperature, with Zhenjiang Aromatic Vinegar
as a sample, and the bran vinegar, brewed from wheat bran at
modest temperature, with Baoning Vinegar as a typical example.
</P>
<P>
The history of Baoning Vinegar dates back some 300 years ago.
Baoning was the name of the county at that time. The well-
preserved "Vinegar Shop Street" in Langzhong still reminds people
of the prosperous scene of that time.
</P>
<P>
Langzhong now has more than 30 vinegar plants. Among them,
Sichuan Baoning Vinegar Co., Ltd is the largest vinegar producer
in southwest China, with an annual production capacity of 15,000
tons of table vinegar.
</P>
<P>
Baoning Vinegar has a stable market especially in southwest
China. One of the reasons why Baoning Vinegar enjoys popular fame
is that the Vinegar is said to be effective in preventing cancer
and many other diseases. The Sichuan Baoning Vinegar Co., Ltd, for
example, has found no cancer case for more than 50 years. Experts
said that this has something to do with the yeast for making the
Baoning Vinegar.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, many new products have been developed from the
Baoning Vinegar, such as the acetic acid drinks, varied fruit
vinegar and special vinegar for drunken people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000823.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
