<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Exposes 330 Drug-Related Cases in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities exposed a
total of 330 narcotic drug related cases in July this year,
seizing 41.83 kilos of opium and 5.21 kilos of heroin in the month,
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure, made by army units, police and the customs, also
include 38.9 kilos of marijuana, 9.47 liters of phensedyl and 244,
147 tablets of stimulant drugs.
</P>
<P>
During the month, the authorities punished 465 people -- 376
men and 89 women -- for being involved in the cases, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics of the Myanmar Central
Committee for Drug Abuse Control, during the first six months of
this year, the country seized a total of 1,283 kilos of narcotic
drugs including 819.5 kilos of opium, 21.41 kilos of heroin, 427.5
kilos of marijuana as well as 3,999 liters of precursor chemicals
and 22.18 million tablets of stimulant drugs.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the authorities exposed a total of 1,
857 drug-related cases, punishing 2,567 drug offenders.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, there remain 89,500 hectares of poppy cultivation in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar is implementing a 255-million-U.S.-dollar 15-
year drug elimination plan which covers 51 cultivating and
producing townships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
