<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Hits Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Hungary is hit by a heat wave
as temperatures go up to 40 degrees Celsius in some parts of the
country, the highest record in history.
</P>
<P>
In Budapest, the temperature reached 38 degrees Celsius on
Monday. In the eastern city of Bekescsaba, the temperature soared
to 42 degrees, even higher than the record 39 degrees in 1943.
</P>
<P>
The heat made more people fall ill and sparked off more fires.
Ambulances were running more frequently, up by 20 percent than
before. Water consumption increased by 30 to 40 percent, according
to local reports.
</P>
<P>
Though the high temperatures dropped since Tuesday, Hungarian
weather forecasters still warned the average temperature will be
higher than normal in the next several days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
