there can be no bail," Judge Timothy Swope was quoted as saying in
the west African nation's capital Monrovia.
</P>
<P>
Gugu Radebe, a freelance South African cameraman, Timothy
Lambon, who holds dual British and South African citizenship,
Sierra Leonean producer Samura Sorious and Briton David Barrie
were arrested in Monrovia last Friday on suspicion of espionage
while filming a three-part documentary for the British television
station Channel 4. (Liberia-Journalist)
