<HEADLINE> Italian Wins Dutch Tour Opening Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Italian Fabrizio Guidi won a
mass sprint finish to the 181.5-km first stage of the Tour of the
Netherlands on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The La Francaise des Jeux team rider beat Dutchman Max van
Heeswijk and Australian Rob McEwen to take the stage from Den
Bosch to Utrecht.
</P>
<P>
Dutchman Erik Dekker, first in Monday's prologue, remained the
overall leader, with a time of four hours 19 minutes and 16
seconds, two seconds ahead of South African Robert Hunter, ninth
on the stage.
</P>
<P>
Van Heeswijk was fifth overall.
</P>
<P>
Dutch rider Rudi Kemna was found guilty of an irregular sprint,
in which he blocked compatriot and Polti team rider Jeroen
Blijlevens. After a successful protest by Blijlevens, Kemna was
relegated to the last place. 
</P>
