<HEADLINE> Hamburg Through Champions League Qualifier with Galatasaray, Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- German side Hamburg SV advanced
to the Champions League finals on Tuesday alongwith UEFA Cup
holders Galatasaray of Turkey, Italian powerhouse AC Milan and
outsiders Shakhtar Donetsk of Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time since 1984 that Hamburg, European
champions in 1983, had qualified for European soccer's top
competition.
</P>
<P>
Hamburg managed a goalless draw with Danish champions Brondby
after they won the first leg of the qualifying round 2-0 to book
their place in the 32-team final competition.
</P>
<P>
Galatasaray were held to a 2-2 draw by St Gallen of Switzerland
but survived the home-and-away qualifiers with a 2-1 win in the
first leg. AC Milan thrashed Dinamo Zagreb of Croatia 3-0 for a 6-
1 aggregate win.
</P>
<P>
Shakhtar took an unlikely victory over Slavia Prague of the
Czech Republic with an injury-time equalizer and an extra-time
winner. 
</P>
