<HEADLINE> Ghana Wants Morocco to Rejoin OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Ghanaian President Jerry John
Rawlings appealed to Morocco to rejoin the Organization of African
Unity (OAU), Ghana News Agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rawlings made the appeal when he met with visiting Moroccan
Foreign Minister Mohamed Benaissa in the capital Accra.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Benaissa transfered a message from King
Mohamed of Morocco to Rawlings.
</P>
<P>
Rawlings said: "It is our genuine desire to see Morocco back to
the OAU. What caused Morocco to leave the continental body could
be resolved."
</P>
<P>
Morocco withdrew from the OAU in 1984 in protest against the
organization's recognition of the Sahara Arab Democratic Republic
(SADR) as an independent state.
</P>
<P>
Moroccan troops and SADR guerrillas have fought battles over
the years and now there is a cease-fire holding to enable the UN
to solve the problem through a referendum to give its inhabitants
the chance to decide whether they want to be part of Morocco or be
independent. 
</P>
