<HEADLINE> Romania to Become 2nd Beer Market in Central Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The beer market in Romania
absorbs annually over 500-600 million U.S. dollars and it is
estimated to become the second distribution market in Central
Europe in less than five years.
</P>
<P>
The annual beer consumption reaches 11.3 hectoliters, with each
Romanian consuming 49 liters of beer annually. With an increase of
4 percent annually, Romania promises to become the second
distribution market in Central Europe, while Poland ranks first.
</P>
<P>
The increase is due to low taxes, a better quality obtained
through investments by beer producers as well as an intense and
professional marketing activity, analysts say.
</P>
<P>
The market is shared by three of the world's largest producers
and a number of domestic companies. 
</P>
