<HEADLINE> Fire Department in Greece on High Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The fire department in Greece has
been on high alert on Wednesday since a heatwave will hit the
country in the next few days.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, temperatures in most parts of the country will
reach 40 degrees and soar to over 40 degrees in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday night, many large forest fires were reported in
various areas of Greece, with the largest one being near the port
town of Lavrion, south of Athens. Currently, hundreds of
firefighters were doing everything they can to place under control
the blaze threatening the installations of the Hellenic Arms
Industry.
</P>
<P>
Fires were also blazing in the areas of Ano Pedina near the
northern city of Ioannina, the southern prefectures of Arcadia and
Ahaia, the Ionian islands of Zakynthos and Corfu and on the island
of Evia.
</P>
<P>
More than 20,000 hectares of forestland and a lot of houses
have been destroyed in the wildfires in the country since the
beginning of July.
</P>
<P>
The Greek authorities blamed both the high temperatures and
arsons for the forest fires around the country. 
</P>
