<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Promulgate New Tobacco Legislation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's new tough
tobacco legislation will be promulgated by October 1, spokesman
for the Health Department Patricia Lambert announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
She said the last minor corrections are being made to the
regulations that will accompany the law, which is expected to be
made public next week.
</P>
<P>
The Tobacco Products Control Amendment Act, approved by South
African Parliament in 1999, will ban tobacco advertising and
publicized sponsorships and prohibit smoking in public places,
including the workplace except as permitted by the South African
Health Minister.
</P>
<P>
The regulations will set out exactly where people may or may
not smoke and will set deadlines for ending advertising and
sponsorship. 
