<HEADLINE> Large Amount of Cocaine Seized in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Angolan National Police announced
here on Thursday that some 62 kilograms of cocaine had been seized
in Luanda since January, the biggest quantity of drugs ever seized
during such a short period in Angola.
</P>
<P>
In the last two months alone, 35 kilograms of cocaine were
captured at the Luanda International Airport, said an official
declaration issued on Thursday by the Angola National Police.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, on August 16, a citizen from the
Democratic Republic of the Congo, resident in Luanda, was arrested
at the Luanda international airport when the police found that
there were 39 packets of cocaine in his bags.
</P>
<P>
Another 17 kilograms of cocaine from Brazil were held in June
this year at the Luanda International Airport. The police
authorities have admitted that there might be a gang of
traffickers based in South Africa and Brazil, with Angola as a
transit point, saying that much of the drug held in Angola comes
from Latin America, mainly from Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
