<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise On Rate Optimism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose
Wednesday as investors continued to show optimism about the
Federal Reserve's decision to leave interest rates alone Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 5.50 at 11,144.65,
extending its gain of 59.34 points in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index rose 52.80 at 4,011.01 and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was up 7.84 at 1,505.97.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index fell as much as 79 points earlier in the session
apparently on profit-taking but the blue chip index bounced back
to the positive territory at the finish.
</P>
<P>
The index gained 59.34 points Tuesday and 33.33 points Monday
in anticipation of the Federal Reserve's decision on steady rates.
After a crucial meeting on the rate issue Tuesday, the central
bank announced its decision to stay on hold amid signs that the U.
S. economy is cooling and inflation remains tame.
</P>
<P>
Analysts believed the Federal Reserve will leave rates
unchanged at least until the American voters go to polls in
November in the presidential election year.
</P>
<P>
Computer maker Hewlett-Packard led the Dow's advance. Banking
stocks and oil shares also rose, helping drive the blue chip index
higher.
</P>
<P>
In the tech sector, Intel and Cisco Systems rose, pushing the
Nasdaq index back to the 4,000 threshold.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 0.60 at 672.22 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 1.35 at 924.10. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 0.42 at 517.88.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,532 down, 1,297 up and 530
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 860.34 million shares from 815.10
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
